C2CRiskPopup:
• P2P trading is a peer-to-peer trading between users. The buyer must pay the seller directly. The seller notifies Gate.io to release the cryptotokens after receiving the payment.
  • Once you've placed the order, ensure you complete the payment within the specified time frame and click "I have paid" right after you've made the payment.
  • Should you fail to confirm payment by clicking "I have paid" within the required time frame, the order will be automatically canceled by the system and deemed invalid. If you have made the payment, do not cancel the order. If you make any mistakes, file an appeal immediately.
  • P2P trading carries risks, please fully understand the rules and beware of scams. Stay reachable and check for SMS or email notifications regularly.

StopOrderTips:
De Stop Loss en Take Profit orders kunnen enkel worden getriggerd wanneer de marktprijs de trigger prijs bereikt.
Wanneer het wordt getriggerd, zal het een order plaatsen tegen de aangewezen prijs, hoeveelheid en richting. De Trigger Prijs kan worden gespecificeerd als ofwel de Laatste Prijs, Referentieprijs of Index Prijs.

Enkel de positie wordt verminderd.

• Het opstartproject bevindt zich nog in de beginfase, factoren zoals de werking en de onderliggende technologie van het project, en andere dergelijke regelgevende activiteiten kunnen aanzienlijke risico's inhouden.
  • Geavanceerde technische en financiële kennis is vereist om de inherente risico's van investeringen in crypto assets te begrijpen en te evalueren.
  • De volatiliteit van de markt is hoog, en de prijs van een token kan drastisch schommelen als gevolg van technische, regelgevende en marketingfactoren enz.
  • Het is mogelijk dat gebruikers niet alle gekochte tokens kunnen opnemen als gevolg van technische problemen van het project op Gate.io.

FeedbackDesc: Gate.io is gericht op het leveren van de beste service in de crypto industrie. We houden ons elke dag volop bezig met vooruitgang en verbetering.
FeedbackIntro: Als één van de vroegste beurzen in de crypto-wereld, is Gate.io vandaag de dag uitgegroeid tot één van de grootste in volume. We kunnen dit niet bereiken zonder de steun en feedback van onze gebruikers. Je waardevolle advies stuwt onze vooruitgang. We willen daarom graag meer van je horen.
FeedbackReport: Email ons op support@mail.gate.io of klik op “Ticket Indienen” om je opmerkingen aan ons door te geven.
SecureCenterReward: Meld beveiligingsgerelateerde bugs en ontvang een beloning van ons
SecureCenterReport: Gelieve ons een bericht te sturen op support@mail.gate.io of dien een ticket in.
SecureCenterHackenproof: Je kunt ervoor kiezen om een kwetsbaarheidsrapport in te dienen bij Hackenproof
SecureCenterAboutContent: Als één van de oudste en grootste exchanges in volume in de crypto wereld, benadrukt Gate.io veiligheid door altijd de blockchain asset veiligheid van gebruikers op de eerste plaats te zetten. We investeren volop in methoden, zowel gecentraliseerd als gedecentraliseerd (Gatechain beveiligingsoplossing), om onze gebruikersfondsen te beschermen. Gate.io is ook bekend als de eerste en unieke exchange die miljoenen dollars "veiligheid en legaliteit fonds" biedt om gebruikers te beschermen. Om de kracht van de hele beveiligingsgemeenschap te benutten, en om de beste experts aan te moedigen om te helpen Gate.io's beveiligingssysteem tot het uiterste te verbeteren, hebben we het programma "Gate.io Bug en Security Suggesties Bounty" opgericht . We bieden een beloning voor iedereen die helpt Gate . io veiliger te maken door ons veiligheidssuggesties en bug analyse aan te bieden .
SecureCenterPromise: Wij beloven je: wanneer je bugrapport wordt ontvangen, zullen onze veiligheidsexpert het bekijken en onmiddellijk evalueren . De eerste melder van een onbekende bug ontvangt een beloning van ons .

SecureCenterHighEg: bijv .: ongeautoriseerde toegang, ernstige SQL injectie, hoog risico op het lekken van informatie .
SecureCenterMediumEg: bijv .: aantasting van het gebruik en de toegang van een deel van onze gebruikers, wijziging van gebruikersinformatie, enz .
SecureCenterLowEg: bijv .: vals bericht / SMS, gelekte niet - gevoelige informatie, etc .

BitcoinHalvingIntroduct: De %s blok beloning halveert elke %s blokken. Na deze halvering wordt de beloning gehalveerd, van %s %s naar %s %s.
WhatHalvingAsk1: Bitcoin halvering, ook wel bekend als bitcoin block reward halvering, betekent dat de beloning voor het maken van nieuwe blokken ongeveer elke vier jaar gehalveerd wordt. Dit betekent dat na de halvering elk gemijnd blok de helft waard is van het bedrag aan bitcoin dat werd toegekend voor de halvering. Toen Bitcoin in 2009 ontstond, was de blokbeloning 50 BTC. De blokbeloning halveert ongeveer elke vier jaar op basis van de bloktijd en zal uiteindelijk zijn eindige totale voorraad van 21 miljoen bereiken.
WhatHalvingAsk2: Tot nu toe is Bitcoin drie keer gehalveerd, in november 2012, juli 2016 en mei 2020. De vierde bitcoin halvering zal naar verwachting plaatsvinden in mei 2024. Tegen die tijd zal de beloning dalen van 6,25 naar 3,125 BTC.
WhyDoesBitcoinHalveAsk: Volgens de vraag- en aanbodtheorie zal er, als een item zijn aanbod in omloop niet beperkt, een overaanbod ontstaan en zal de prijs dalen. Dit concept is ook van toepassing op bitcoin. Het gebruik van halvering om de hoeveelheid en circulatie te beperken kan de schaarste vergroten en het waardevoller maken. De blokbeloning van Bitcoin is geprogrammeerd om elke 210.000 blokken te halveren, wat de inflatie kan vertragen en nieuwe munten op een gecontroleerde manier in omloop kan brengen. Het halveren van Bitcoin is ook een onderscheidend kenmerk dat het onderscheidt van traditionele fiatvaluta's.
HistoricalBitcoinHalvingSchedule1: Satoshi Nakamoto publiceerde "Een Peer-to-Peer Electronisch Cash Systeem" en introduceerde daarmee voor het eerst het concept van Bitcoin.
HistoricalBitcoinHalvingSchedule2: Satoshi Nakamoto mijnde het genesis-blok en bitcoin kwam ter wereld. Op dat moment was de blokbeloning 50 BTC.
HistoricalBitcoinHalvingSchedule3: Satoshi Nakamoto heeft bepaald dat Bitcoin elke 210.000 blokken halveert, totdat alle 21 miljoen bitcoin zijn gemijnd, wat naar schatting in het jaar 2140 zal gebeuren.
HistoricalBitcoinHalvingSchedule4: Eerste Bitcoin halvering. De blokbeloning werd verlaagd naar 25 BTC
HistoricalBitcoinHalvingSchedule5: Tweede Bitcoin halvering. De blokbeloning werd verlaagd tot 12,5 BTC
HistoricalBitcoinHalvingSchedule6: Derde Bitcoin halvering. De blokbeloning werd verlaagd tot 6,25 BTC.
HistoricalBitcoinHalvingSchedule7: De komende vierde halvering zal naar verwachting plaatsvinden in mei 2024. Na deze halvering zal de blokbeloning 3,125 BTC bedragen.

AboutUsText:
Gate.io werd opgericht in 2013 en is één van 's werelds toonaangevende blockchain digitale asset handelsplatformen. Diep gecultiveerd in de industrie voor 8 jaar, zijn we toegewijd in het creëren van een veilige, stabiele, transparante en betrouwbare cryptocurrency ervaring. Sinds onze oprichting hebben we altijd aangedrongen op het principe: 'veiligheid eerst, gebruikers eerst, geen fraude, geen kwaadwillige acties, zorgvuldige selectie van projecten en nul noteringskosten'. Gate.io is meerdere malen geselecteerd als wereldwijde top 10 crypto exchange voor authentiek handelsvolume, stortingsvolume, cybersecurity en transparantie. Vanaf 2020 is Gate.io het allereerste mainstream blockchain-asset handelsplatform dat gecontroleerd bewijs van 100% onderpand biedt.

Gate.io biedt een breed scala aan producten en professionele handelsfuncties, terwijl het wereldwijd verspreide zakelijke en technologische diensten zoals Wallet.io, GateChain, Blockchain Research Instituut, etc. exploiteert. Via ons Web en APP platform, bedienen we meer dan 3 miljoen gebruikers verspreid over 130 landen. Op de Coin Market biedt Gate.io handels- en beleggingsdiensten aan voor meer dan 400 handelsparen, met een gemiddeld dagelijks bezoekvolume van meer dan 6 miljoen en een gemiddeld transactievolume van ongeveer 400 miljoen USD per dag.

Het team van Gate.io heeft vele jaren ervaring met blockchain, waarbij de belangrijkste leden van ons team de topexperts zijn op verschillende gebieden. Op dit moment heeft Gate.io onafhankelijke zakelijke en operationele centra in China, Zuid-Korea, Canada, Singapore en vele andere landen.

Om onze gemeenschap te versterken en gebruikers in staat te stellen om deel te nemen aan het proces van de notering van nieuwe munten, heeft Gate.io een nieuwe functie geïmplementeerd genaamd 'listing vote'. swapQuestion_value_1: Liquidity mining is een manier om een passief inkomen te verdienen met crypto door cryptocurrencies te verpanden of in te zetten in een liquiditeitspool. Dit is een nieuwe trend in gedecentraliseerde financiering (DeFi), die beleggers in staat stelt een maximaal rendement te verdienen op hun digitale assets. Liquidity mining staat open voor iedereen en is de kern van gedecentraliseerde financiële modellen. In een notendop betekent dit dat je rijkelijk beloond kunt worden door simpelweg je cryptocurrency te staken.
swapQuestion_value_2: Liquidity tokens (liquidity providing token, ook bekend als LP token) verwijzen naar de tokens die gegenereerd worden nadat liquiditeits bieders investeren en inzetten in een Liquidity Pool. In een Liquidity Pool, hoe meer geld gebruikers investeren, hoe hoger hun aandeel van liquiditeit tokens zal zijn. Tegelijkertijd zijn LP-tokens ook een wiskundig bewijs van de assets in de huidige pool en deelnemers moeten LP-tokens houden om hun ingezette assets in de pool terug te krijgen.
swapQuestion_value_3: Dit verwijst naar een niet-permanent verlies veroorzaakt door volatiliteit in een handelspaar wanneer beleggers middelen inzetten in een liquiditeitspool. Bij een impermanent loss wordt de huidige waarde van het vermogen van een belegger vergeleken met de waarde van het vermogen als het niet in een liquiditeitspool was gestort.
swapQuestion_4: Wat is een impermanent loss over de dagelijkse inkomsten?
swapQuestion_value_4: Impermanent loss over de dagelijkse inkomsten wordt gebruikt om te schatten hoeveel daginkomsten het impermanent loss kunnen compenseren dat door de koerswijziging wordt veroorzaakt.

WhyUpgradeETH2: Waarom moet ETH geüpgraded worden naar ETH 2.0?
UpgradeReason1:
1. Hogere Schaalbaarheid
ETH1.0 kan slechts 15 transacties per seconde aan. De geüpgrade ETH2.0 zal de belasting van het netwerk spreiden over 64 (misschien meer in de toekomst) nieuwe chains. Theoretisch is ETH2.0 in staat om duizenden of zelfs tienduizenden transacties per seconde te verwerken. Bovendien wordt het probleem van de overconcentratie van de hoofdnetwerkcomputers opgelost en wordt de schaalbaarheid verder verbeterd.
UpgradeReason2:
2. Duurzaamheid van het milieu.
Momenteel evolueert Ethereum in de richting van PoW-beveiliging. Hoewel PoW grote voordelen biedt wat betreft veiligheid en decentralisatie, is het duur voor nodes om de veiligheid van het netwerk te verzekeren. Uiteindelijk kan slechts één node de correcte hashwaarde vinden en de blokbeloning krijgen. Maar alle wereldwijd deelnemende nodes hebben enorme rekenkracht en elektriciteit nodig, wat niet alleen inefficiënt is, maar ook een verspilling van milieubronnen. Bij het upgraden naar het PoS-consensusmechanisme zal ETH niet langer afhankelijk zijn van enorme rekenkracht en elektriciteit om het netwerk in stand te houden en te laten functioneren, maar zal het vertrouwen op de verificatie van het aandeel van de token om blokken te creëren en te verhandelen in de chain.
LikeETH1: Net als ETH1.0, is ETH2.0 opgedeeld in verschillende fasen. De belangrijkste daarvan zijn fase 0, fase 1 en fase 2.
StagePhase0: Fase 0: Beacon ChainDit is de allereerste fase van ETH2.0, waarin de beacon chain wordt geïmplementeerd. Als een nieuwe chain is de beacon chain verantwoordelijk voor de deelname van validators aan stakings, om zo het netwerk in stand te houden. Het is ook het order- en controlecentrum van het ETH2.0 eco. Het ETH2.0-netwerk in fase 0 ondersteunt geen functies zoals smart contracts, asset overdracht, enzovoort. Het enige beschikbare programma is verificatie. Gebruikers kunnen hun assets niet overdragen naar een beurs in deze fase.
StagePhase1: Phase 1: ShardingThe main goal of phase 1 is to integrate ETH1.0 with ETH2.0. A shard chain essentially is an expansion mechanism of the ETH network, which splits the ETH blockchain into 64 different chains and distributes the data processing tasks to many nodes, allowing them to process these data parallel. Each sharding chain acts as a diversion lane of the congested ETH networks to dramatically improve the processing capacity of the network and produce a higher throughput. Click to get the sharding roadmap: https://eth.wiki/en/sharding/sharding-roadmap
StagePhase2: Fase 2: UitvoeringDe huidige definities en functies van fase 2 worden nog onderzocht. In fase 2 zullen de sharding-functies uitgebreid worden verbeterd. Elke shard zal EVM besturen op basis van eWASM en zal compatibel zijn met smart contracts. Tegelijkertijd kan het overdrachten uitvoeren, opnemen en cross-shard overdragen. Deze fase zal de integratie van ETH1.0 en ETH2.0 afronden en een einde maken aan het PoW-consensusmechanisme.
WhatIseWASM: eWASM (ETH WASM) is ETH2.0's oplossing gericht op het knelpuntenprobleem van de virtuele ETH-machine (EVM). EVM's zijn verantwoordelijk voor de interne toestand van het ETH-netwerk en al zijn berekeningen, wat een belangrijke impact heeft op de snelheid van het uitvoeren van taken en de algemene beschikbaarheid van het netwerk. De eWASM is een open standaardinstructieset van de W3C-communitygroep en is ontwikkeld door topingenieurs van Google, Microsoft, Apple, enz. Het ondersteunt traditionele programmeertalen, bijvoorbeeld C/C++, en 64-bit gegevensverwerking. Het zal ook de verwerkingssnelheid en doorvoercapaciteit van het netwerk verhogen, evenals de veiligheid en beschikbaarheid.
BecomeValidator: Hoe word ik een validator van ETH2.0?
DepositContract: Eerst moeten gebruikers 32 ether inzetten op het deposit contract:
RunBothTerminals: Dan moeten ze tegelijkertijd zowel ETH1.0 als ETH2.0 terminals draaien om een validator te worden. Als validator moet de node voor een lange tijd online blijven. Validators krijgen een beloning van ETH wanneer ze met succes één blok hebben geverifieerd, met een inzetrente van ongeveer 5-10%. Als de validator echter de taak van verificatie van het door de beacon chain toegewezen ETH-netwerk mist omdat hij offline is, zal hij een boete krijgen. Kwaadwillige bedoelingen en verkeerde verificaties zullen leiden tot confiscatie van de 32 ingezette Ether.
IrreversibleTransaction: De ETH die is ingezet op het deposit contract is een onomkeerbare transactie. Validators zullen de mogelijkheid hebben om hun fondsen over te maken totdat ETH2.0 fase 1 bereikt. Het duurt dus nog twee of drie jaar voordat ETH2.0 volledig toegang heeft tot sharding en smart contracts, wat betekent dat validators het risico lopen dat ze minstens 2 jaar lang geen ETH kunnen opnemen. Bovendien zal ETH, eenmaal verhypothekeerd aan de beacon chain, BETH genereren en niet kunnen terugkeren naar de ETH1.0 mainchain. Als ETH2.0 er niet in slaagt te upgraden, kunnen er verliezen optreden. Als gevolg hiervan wordt het niet aanbevolen dat gewone gebruikers validators worden.
EthereumUpgrade: Volgens nieuws over de Ethereum-upgrade heeft het stakingscontract voor ETH2.0 de minimale stortingsvereiste bereikt voor de lancering van fase 0 op 1 december 2020. Na de lancering van fase 0, konden ETH-houders deelnemen aan PoS staking door hun ETH te storten op ETH2.0 om beloningen te verdienen.
Eth2Staking: Deelnemen aan ETH2.0 staking is niet gemakkelijk. Het vereist een hogere technische expertise en vereist een lange stakingstijd (naar schatting 1-2 jaar, wat kan variëren naarmate ETH2.0 zich ontwikkelt). Bovendien moet je een validator op zowel de ETH1.0 chain als de ETH2.0 Beacon Chain tegelijkertijd laten draaien en daarbij een stabiele staking-status handhaven. Anders kunnen je fondsen in staking boetes in rekening worden gebracht.
LowerStakingThreshold:
Vanwege de hoge toetredingsdrempels is eth2 staking niet geschikt voor elke gebruiker. Om alle gebruikers een kans te geven deel te nemen aan eth2 staking, zal Gate.io een flexibele eth2 staking oplossing bieden aan gebruikers, gebaseerd op onze stabiel werkende Ethereum infrastructuur en maturity asset management oplossing.
        Met deze oplossing kunnen gebruikers een staking beloning verdienen terwijl ze hun ETH niet voor een lange tijd in eth2 hoeven vast te zetten of zich zorgen hoeven te maken over eth2 boetes.
        Hieronder vind je meer details over onze eth2 staking oplossing.
LowerThreshold1: Gate.io zal ETH2 tokens noteren, wat het certificaat zal zijn voor gebruikers om deel te nemen aan ETH2 staking. 1 ETH2 vertegenwoordigt 1 ETH vergrendeld in ETH2 staking. ETH2 bezitten is gelijk aan deelnemen aan ETH2 staking.
LowerThreshold2: Gebruikers kunnen ETH2 vrijwillig kopen of verkopen op de USDT- en ETH-markten.
LowerThreshold3: Gate.io zal de netto-inkomsten (staking inkomsten min de kosten) van eth2 staking uitkeren aan ETH2 houders wanneer eth2 staking begint.
LowerThreshold4: De staking-beloning zal in de vorm van ETH2.O worden uitgekeerd, gebaseerd op de gemiddelde ETH2-assets van gebruikers over een periode van 14 dagen.
LowerThreshold5: Op dit moment wachten validators in de rij voor de kans om te staken op ETH2. Het kan enkele dagen duren om te beginnen met staken na de lancering van ETH2 (de vertraging kan variëren, afhankelijk van de lengte van de wachtlijst).
LowerThreshold6: De jaarlijkse beloning % van ETH2 staking is gerelateerd aan de hoeveelheid ETH die gestaked wordt. De opbrengst neigt hoger te zijn in een vroeg stadium omdat er minder ETH wordt ingezet. Op lange termijn zal de opbrengst naar verwachting stabiel blijven rond de 5%-10%.

LendQ1: Hoe mijn winst berekenen in Crypto Lening?
LendA1:
Winst in Crypto Leningen is de leenrente, die per uur wordt berekend.
Berekeningsregels voor leenuren: de minimum berekeningsperiode is 4 uur
1) voor leenaanbiedingen minder dan 4 uur: wordt berekend als een vaste 4 uur
2) voor leenaanbiedingen meer dan 4 uur: wordt berekend volgens de werkelijke tijd, met een afrondingsmethode (minder dan 1 uur wordt berekend als 1 uur)
Interestformule: interest = leenbedrag * dagrentevoet / 24 * leenuren
LendQ2: Wanneer wordt mijn winst uitgekeerd bij Crypto Leningen?
LendA2: De aanvankelijke duur van de lening is een vaste 10 dagen. De lener wordt onderworpen aan een verplichte terugbetaling voor achterstallige leningen. De hoofdsom & rente zullen terugkeren naar het spot account van de lener nadat de terugbetaling is gebeurd, tenzij de optie 'Auto-vernieuwing/Auto-order' is aangevinkt tijdens het plaatsen van de leningaanbieding. De lener kan vooraf terugbetalen, en als dat zo is, is de werkelijke duur van de lening afhankelijk van de datum van terugbetaling.
LendA3: Nadat de lener heeft terugbetaald, worden commissiekosten (maximaal 18%) in rekening gebracht van de verdiende rente, en gebruikers genieten van een VIP-korting. Raadpleeg het Help Center voor gedetailleerde korting.

Futures.Bonus.Usage.Scenario: Kan worden gebruikt bij het verhandelen van %s perpetual contracten
Futures.Bonus.Rules:
1. De futuresbonus kan worden gebruikt als margin, ter compensatie van accountverliezen en ter financiering van betalingen bij het verhandelen van futures.

2. Op dit moment kan de futuresbonus alleen in bepaalde futuresmarkten worden gebruikt. Als er lopende orders of open posities zijn in niet-ondersteunde futuresmarkten, moet u deze orders annuleren of deze posities sluiten voordat u de bonus kunt gebruiken in een ondersteunde markt, anders wordt de bonus ongeldig en kan deze niet worden gebruikt.

3. Nadat u de futuresbonus op de ondersteunde markt met succes hebt toegepast, kunt u geen orders meer plaatsen op niet-ondersteunde markten totdat de bonus is opgebruikt.

4. Markten die momenteel de futuresbonus ondersteunen: %s
Quant.Trial.Fund.Rules:
1. Quant-proeffonds kan worden gebruikt om verlies te compenseren, of voor handelskosten, betalingen of investeringskapitaal.

2. Quant-proeffonds wordt gebruikt voorafgaand aan het eigen vermogen van de gebruiker.

3. Inkomsten van Quant-proeffonds kunnen niet worden ingetrokken. De inkomsten worden na het verlopen van het Quant-proeffonds automatisch overgemaakt naar het spotaccount.

4. Quant-proeffonds vervalt binnen 7 dagen vanaf de datum waarop het wordt vrijgegeven. Elk ongebruikt deel wordt op de vervaldatum teruggestuurd naar Gate.io.
Zero.Interest.Voucher.Usage.Scenario: Kan gebruikt worden bij het lenen in %s-modus
Zero.Interest.Voucher.Rules:
1. Nulrentevoucher wordt gebruikt op de markt voor marginleningen om af te zien van rente op leningen.

2. Door Nulrentevoucher te gebruiken voor marginleningen, zal het geleende bedrag binnen het quotum en de periode geen rente genereren (het ongebruikte deel vervalt) en zal het overtollige deel rente opleveren.

Punten kunnen worden gebruikt om kosten voor spot- en futurehandel te betalen; punten zijn niet overdraagbaar.
Er zijn twee manieren om de details van punten te bekijken

1. Selecteer Punten in Beloningscentrum

2. Ga naar de pagina Puntenbeheer

Stable-Coin-FAQ-Title1: Waarom zou ik een stablecoin zoals %s kopen?
Stable-Coin-FAQ-Title2: Hoe kan de waarde van stablecoins zoals %s worden behouden?
Other-Coin-FAQ-Title1: Wat is bepalend voor de prijs van %s?
Other-Coin-FAQ-Title2: Wat is de hoogste prijs van %s geweest tot nu toe?
Other-Coin-FAQ-Title3: Wat is de laagste prijs van %s geweest tot nu toe?
Stable-Coin-FAQ-Content1: Een stablecoin zoals %s fungeert voornamelijk als ruilmiddel in de cryptocommunity, waardoor gebruikers in de community op elk moment cryptovaluta's naar keuze kunnen kopen en verkopen. Verder bieden stablecoins zoals %s een financiële hedge voor mensen uit economieën met een hoge inflatie en een stabielere valuta in de vorm van crypto.
Stable-Coin-FAQ-Content2: Het is belangrijk om te onthouden dat zelfs een stabiele valuta zoals %s onderworpen kan zijn aan extreme marktomstandigheden, juridisch beleid, projectteambeheer en andere onvoorspelbare factoren. Daarom is het belangrijk om uw eigen financiële portfolio en risiconiveau te beheren. Gebruikers wordt aangeraden om zelf onderzoek te doen bij beleggingsbeslissingen op de cryptomarkt.
Stable-Coin-FAQ-Content3: Er zijn drie soorten stablecoins op de markt: fiat-backed, crypto-collateralized en algoritmisch.
Stable-Coin-FAQ-Content4: Fiat-backed stablecoins zijn gekoppeld aan geldreserves van een fiatvaluta zoals USD of EUR, terwijl crypto-collateralized stablecoins gekoppeld zijn aan bezit van andere cryptovaluta's zoals BTC of ETH in plaats van aan fiatvaluta's.
Stable-Coin-FAQ-Content5: De meest controversiële zijn algoritmische stablecoins, die gebouwd zijn op een blockchain en vertrouwen op het algoritme van vraag en aanbod om de prijskoppeling 1:1 te behouden. Als de vraag toeneemt om de prijs op te drijven, geeft het protocol meer aanbod uit om de prijs tot de vastgelegde prijs van $ 1,00 te verlagen en omgekeerd.
Other-Coin-FAQ-Content1: Er zijn twee denkrichtingen bij het bepalen van de prijs van %s.
Other-Coin-FAQ-Content2: Aan de hand van de intrinsieke waarde: het gaat hierbij om on-chain statistieken, projectgegevens en financiële gegevens van %s, algemeen bekend als fundamentele analyse. De wet van vraag en aanbod, tokenomics, usecases, projectroadmaps en de betrokken regelgeving en het bestuur zouden de waarde van %s op de lange termijn beïnvloeden.
Other-Coin-FAQ-Content3: Aan de hand van prijsactie: de technische analyse wordt hoofdzakelijk uitgevoerd via patronen in kaarsgrafieken en technische indicatoren zoals MACD, RSI en de bollinger bands, en voorspelt de prijs van %s op basis van de veronderstelling dat de geschiedenis zich herhaalt. Aangezien de kaarsgrafieken een algemene weergave zijn van de marktgevoeligheid, kunnen nieuwsberichten en de stemming in de community ook belangrijke factoren voor de prijsactie zijn voor %s.
Other-Coin-FAQ-Content4: HODLers geven de voorkeur aan het langetermijnkarakter van fundamentele analyse, terwijl kortetermijnhandelaren meer vertrouwen op technische analyse. In werkelijkheid kunnen beide analyses samen interessante scenario's opleveren voor %s en de cryptovalutamarkt als geheel.
Other-Coin-FAQ-Content5: %s1 bereikte het hoogste punt ooit van %s2 in %s3 en wordt momenteel verhandeld op %s4.
Other-Coin-FAQ-Content6: In %s1 bereikte %s2 het laagste punt ooit van %s3.
Other-Coin-FAQ-Content7: Het is belangrijk om te onthouden dat %s, net als alle andere cryptovaluta's, onderworpen zijn aan extreme marktomstandigheden, juridisch beleid, projectteambeheer en andere onvoorspelbare factoren. Daarom fluctueren cryptovaluta's sterk en is het belangrijk om uw eigen risiconiveau te beheren. Gebruikers wordt aangeraden om zelf onderzoek te doen bij beleggingsbeslissingen op de cryptomarkt.

BCD_Halving_Description:
"Bitcoin Diamond (BCD)" is een vork van Bitcoin die plaatsvindt op de vooraf bepaalde hoogte van blok 495.866 op 24 november 2017. Het totale bedrag van BCD is 210 miljoen. 170 miljoen BCD zal worden aangeboden aan Bitcoin-houders in de verhouding van 10 BCD tot 1 BTC. De resterende 40 miljoen zal automatisch worden overgemaakt naar de community rewards pool als eerbetoon en mining. Met een grafische mining rig, biedt BCD lage overdrachtskosten, schaalbaarheid en ondersteuning voor meerdere betalingstoepassingen.

De BCD Foundation heeft samen met de wereldwijde gemeenschap de ontwikkeling afgerond van E-commerce en betalingstoepassingen voor KMO's, zoals BCDpay, BCDbazaar en BCDapp. De werking wordt geleidelijk aan uitgebreid.

waitlist_faq_a1: The Gate Card is a payment card that is linked to your Gate account. It can be used to make purchases online or in-person, withdraw cash from ATMs, and perform other financial transactions.
waitlist_faq_q2: How do I get a Gate Card?
waitlist_faq_a2: To get a Gate Card, you must first create a Gate account and complete KYC. Once your account is created, you can order a card from within the Gate app or Gate website.
waitlist_faq_q3: How and Where can I spend my crypto with the Gate Card?
waitlist_faq_a3: The new Gate Card offers users a simple method to convert their crypto assets into fiat for in-store and online purchases, providing a seamless and secure way for users to spend their cryptocurrency at 80 million merchant locations that accept Visa worldwide.
waitlist_faq_q4: Which country/region does the Gate Card support?
waitlist_faq_a4: Gate Card is available in most countries in the European Economic Area.
waitlist_faq_q5: How do I report a lost or stolen Gate Card?
waitlist_faq_a5: If your Gate Card is lost or stolen, you should report it immediately by contacting Gate customer support. They will be able to assist you with canceling the card and issuing a new one.
waitlist_faq_q6: How do I check my balance and transaction history?
waitlist_faq_a6: You can check your Gate Card balance and transaction history through the Gate app. Simply log in to your account and navigate to the card section to view your current balance and recent transactions.
waitlist_faq_q7: What are the associated fees of Gate Card?
waitlist_faq_q10: How to Bind Gate Card to Google Pay?
waitlist_faq_a10: You can bind your Gate Card to Google Pay by downloading and opening the Google Pay App on your Android mobile device. Add Gate Card details to Google Pay. After successful binding, no PIN is required for purchases with the virtual Gate card on Google Pay. Apple Pay will be coming soon.

faq.1.1: Simple Earn matches users' idle funds with loan demand to help generate passive income on users’ lent assets. Instead of using a fixed interest rate throughout the entire loan duration, Simple Earn settles interest with updated execution interest rate hourly based on market conditions automatically, thus providing more flexibility and increased capital efficiency for lenders. As a lender, you can join the program any time and receive a better interest rate than you preset, with your lent funds becoming accessible again with a maximum delay of 1-hour when you exit.
faq.2.1: At the end of an hour (also the very start of the next hour , ie,X:00:00), a single interest rate will be figured out as the execution interest rate and applied retroactively to all eligible lending over the past hour. The interest is offered in tranches based on whether the funds’ minimum interest rate is below, equal to or above the execution interest rate. Funds provided with the minimum interest rate below the execution interest rate will receive interest first. If there is any remaining interest, they will go to funds provided with the minimum interest rate equal to the execution interest rate, on a first-come, first-served basis. Funds provided with the minimum interest rate above the execution interest rate will not receive any interest. If your assets are borrowed successfully on the hour at T, you will receive the interest earned during the following hour at T+1. However, if you redeem your assets before the T+1 settlement, you will not receive any interest for the past hour. Interest received every hour will be invested automatically to earn compound interest. You can redeem both principal and interest at redemption.
faq.3.1: You can join or exit Simple Earn anytime you want. Redeemed assets will be returned to your account immediately. Please note that if you apply to redeem assets when the Borrowed Percentage is 100%, which means all lending offers are borrowed, you will receive the assets once there are available funds in the pool. Please wait patiently and interest will keep accruing during this period.

gate_otc_page_description: Gate OTC provides HNWI and institutions a safe and secure channel for crypto-fiat on-ramp and off-ramp via Gate’s bank account. Major currencies such as USD included.
gate_otc_faq_a1: To use Gate OTC services, you first need to register a Gate.io account and verify your identity. Once the KYC verification is done, follow the instructions to buy/sell cryptocurrencies with fiat.
gate_otc_faq_q2: What fiat and cryptocurrency can I trade on Gate OTC?
gate_otc_faq_a2: Gate OTC supports the trade of various legal tenders, including AUD, CAD, EUR, GBP, HKD, JPY, SGD, USD, etc.. These fiat currencies can be converted to USDT / USDC / BTC /ETH, etc. More currencies will be added to the tradeable list shortly. If you need to trade any currency that is not on our list, please contact the OTC team at any time.
gate_otc_faq_q3: When will the funds arrive in your account?
gate_otc_faq_a3: Crediting time of funds depends on the deposit/withdrawal method you use and the transaction processing speed of the bank or payment service provider. Under normal circumstances, it takes the bank 1-3 working days to process the transfer. We now support DBS intra-bank transfer, which can deliver the funds to your account as fast as within 24 hours.
gate_otc_faq_q4: What are the quotes for OTC trade? Are any fees charged for the service?
gate_otc_faq_a4: Gate OTC is subject to the quotes published each day. No fee will be charged for the service.
gate_otc_faq_q5: Is there a minimum or maximum order amount requirement?
gate_otc_faq_a5: Gate OTC requires the min order amount to be no less than 30,000 USDT. There is no imposed limit on the maximum order amount. To place a larger order, please contact Gate OTC team, which will formulate a detailed transaction plan according to your actual needs.
gate_otc_faq_q6: What KYC verification documents need to be provided?
gate_otc_faq_a6_1: Gate OTC Individual KYC Documents List
gate_otc_faq_q7: Can I trade with different bank accounts?
gate_otc_faq_a7: Yes, any individual/institution who has passed the Gate OTC KYC verification can use multiple bank accounts under their names to trade OTC.
gate_otc_faq_a8: Afghanistan, Albania, Bahamas, Barbados, Belarus, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Burundi, Cambodia, Canada, Central African Republic, China, Crimea region of Ukraine, Cuba, Democratic People's Republic of Korea (North Korea), Democratic Republic of the Congo, Ghana, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Haiti, Iran, Iraq, Jamaica, Japan, Lebanon, Libya, Macau (China), Mali, Malta, Myanmar, Nicaragua, Pakistan, Panama, Russia, Somalia, South Sudan, Sudan, Syria, Nida and Tobago, Uganda, United States, Vanuatu, Yemen, Zaire, Zimbabwe
gate_otc_faq_q9: What is the process of trading OTC?
gate_otc_faq_a9: Please create a Gate account first and verify your identity by following the prompts. After completing KYC, you will be able to trade through online quotation mode or contact our customer support for manual trading.
gate_otc_faq_q10: Which banks are supported for OTC?
gate_otc_faq_a10: Gate OTC now supports multiple banks worldwide, which now support funds transfers with all mainstream banks on the market, including neo and digital banks.

express.banner.title: Buy Crypto Safely, Quickly and Easily
express.banner.subTitle: We support over 300 payment methods and nearly 100 fiat currencies.
express.faq.a1: You can conveniently buy cryptocurrencies on Gate.io as the platform supports about 100 fiat currencies and over 300 payment methods, including credit and debit cards. Alternatively, use the P2P trading function on Gate.io to trade cryptocurrencies directly with other users around the world.
express.faq.q2: How to buy cryptocurrencies on Gate.io?
express.faq.a2: Gate.io supports a variety of payment methods, including debit and cards as well as bank transfers. You can buy cryptocurrency on Gate.io by selecting the cryptocurrency of your choice and your preferred payment method.
express.faq.q3: Is it safe to buy cryptocurrencies via Gate.io?
express.faq.a3:
Founded in 2013, Gate.io is a leading digital asset trading platform in the world based on real trading volume.
As the earliest centralized exchange in the world to provide 100% proof of reserves, Gate.io is legally registered in many countries around the world and provides safe, reliable, real and transparent digital asset trading services to tens of millions of users worldwide. We have adopted stringent security measures, including multi-factor authentication, cold wallet storage and real-time monitoring, to protect users' assets and transaction security. In addition, Gate.io conducts frequent security audits to ensure the health of the platform and privacy protection of user data.
express.faq.q4: Points to Note on P2P Transfers
express.faq.a4:
1. Please do not use sensitive descriptions such as BTC/USDT/Gate.io during the transfer process to prevent situations such as your remittance being intercepted or your bank card being frozen. If there is a delay in the transfer as a result, the seller may refuse the trade.
2. Please use bank cards matching your platform name to perform the remittance, failing which the seller may refuse the trade and file a complaint.
3. Please ensure timely completion of the remittance, especially if the transaction amount is above 50,000 CNY, or if remittance is made after 17:00, or if remittance is made on public holidays. If there is undue delay, the seller has the right to refuse the trade.
4. Please refer to the Gate.io help center if you have any further questions on P2P transfers.

Futures Bonus Deposit Rules:
1. After receiving the Deposit Voucher, you need to manually click on "Deposit Now" to deposit it to your Futures Bonus.

2. You need to switch to the Futures Bonus Trading Mode before using the Futures Bonus.

3. Futures Bonus can be used as margin to offset realized losses when you are trading futures.

4. Bonus Trading Mode is separate from Futures Account, so their positions won't hedge against each other.

5. Assets cannot be transferred in/out in Bonus Trading Mode.

6. You are not responsible for any loss incurred from Bonus Trading; earnings from it will be credited to your Futures Account.

7. Validity period of the Bonus is from its successful deposit till its expiry. Upon expiry, the Bonus will become invalid and the open positions will be closed at market price.

8. Only one Bonus Deposit Voucher can be used at a time.

9. If you want to use other Bonus Deposit Voucher, you can manually close the position and destroy the Bonus currently in use.

10. For markets currently support Futures Bonus, please refer to the trading list.

unified.explore.mutiple: Explore multiple trading types with one account.
unified.hedge.risks: Hedge risks and allow to open new positions with unrealized profits.
unified.diff.between: Difference between the Unified Account and the Classic Account
unified.experience.more: Experience more trading types with margin sharing in one account. No need to transfer funds.
unified.hedge.various: Hedge various risks on the level of the entire portfolio and PNL are offset, thus reducing the margin adjustment operations in a volatile market.
unified.separate.account: Separate accounts for different trading types, isolating funds and risks from each other, but you need to manage your own trading portfolio.
unified.with.risk: With isolated trading types, the risk on one account is limited to the specific account only. One account’s loss won’t have a ripple effect on others.
unified.one.stop: One-stop experience of multiple trading types
unified.you.can.trade: You can directly trade Spot, Spot Margin Trading, USDT Perpetual Futures, Delivery Futures, and Options under the Unified Account and avoid frequent funds transfer among different accounts.
unified.60.coins: 60+ coins are supported to be collateralized. With margin sharing and PNL offset among different trading types, unrealized profits can be used to open new positions, which greatly enhances the capital efficiency.
unifed.liquidation.classic: Liquidation in Classic Account can lead to greater losses as risks are not hedged over the entire portfolio; whereas for Unified Account, as long as the Account Initial Margin Level and Account Maintenance Margin Level meet certain requirements, you can continue to open/hold positions. Your account will not be liquidated easily even if you have suffered great losses in one specific market.
unified.fully.control: Fully control over asset allocation for different businesses. Profit and loss in one account will not have a ripple effect on another.
unified.spot.and.margin: Spot Trading and Spot Margin Trading
unified.shared.margin.usd: Share margin in USD value among different trading types.
unified.pnl.are.offset: PNL are offset and allow to open new positions with unrealized profits.
unified.fully.hedge.risks: Fully hedge risks for all positions of the underlying crypto and only require margin for the naked exposure.
unified.spot.margin.trade.span: 「Spot Margin Trading」is to conduct margin trading in spot markets, which is only supported in the Unified Account. Once you have enabled Spot Margin Trading, assets in the Unified Account can be pledged as margin.
unified.when.you.place: When you place an order in spot markets, the system will auto-borrow funds you need. In this way, you have the potential to earn high reward with a small amount of investment.
unified.assets.in.unified: Assets in the Unified Account can be pledged as margin. Buy or sell coins with a leverage up to 3x in spot markets.
unified.risk.control.mode: Risk Control Mechanism for Unified Account - Multi-Currency Margin Mode
unified.cac.margin: Calculate margin over the entire account and share margin among different trading types.
unified.liq.is.triggered: Liquidation is triggered when the Account Maintenance Margin Level hits 100%.
unified.all.assets.value: All assets' value in the Unified Account will be converted to USD value to calculate the Account Initial Margin Level (AIML) and Account Maintenance Margin Level (AMML).
unified.when.the.maintenance: When the Maintenance Margin Level reaches 100%, part of positions will be liquidated to release more margin and liquidation will immediately stop once the Account Maintenance Margin Level is above 100%.
unified.cal.the.liq.price: Calculate the liquidation price based on position initial margin, maintenance margin and available balance.
unified.when.price.span: When the mark price reaches the liquidation price, all positions will be liquidated.
unified.understand.unified: Understand Unified Account in 3 minutes and explore more trading strategies.
unified.what.is.unified: What is Unified Account, and how to quickly start using it?
unified.what.are.req: What are the requirements to be a Unified Account user?
unifed.you.vip: Your VIP tier should be 2 or above and your spot assets should be at least 500 USD.
unified.how.many: How many account modes are there in Unified Account?
unifeid.there.are.three: There are three account modes in Unified Account: Classic Spot Mode, Multi-Currency Margin Mode, and Portfolio Margin Mode.
unfied.spot.enable.funds: Spot Margin Trading is only accessible after you upgrade to the Unified Account. Enable「Margin Trading」on the spot trading page and the system will auto-borrow the funds you need. Interest is calculated and deducted at the start of the next hour after you successfully borrowed funds.
unified.what.lab.acount: What are the liabilities in Unified Account?
unified.lab.unified.account: Liabilities in Unified Account include: Spot Borrowed, negative balance caused by interest deduction (due to insufficient balance), Futures Unrealized PNL.
unified.interset.settlement: Interest = Principal * Hourly Borrowing Rate (1+18%). Interest is calculated and deducted at the start of the very next hour after you successfully borrow funds. If you have repaid your loans before the hourly interest settlement, no interest will be charged.
unified.how.repay.account: How to repay liabilities in Unified Account?
unified.for.now: For now, you can only repay the Spot Borrowed manually. The auto-repayment function is not available yet. Stay tuned.
unified.for.negative.balance: For negative balance caused by interest deduction or futures losses, your liabilities can be auto-repaid by transferring in or buying corresponding coins.
clearNegativebalance: Make sure no spot assets has negative balance.

Price.Trending.title.1: Popular Crypto Today: Prices, Charts & Data
Price.Trending.tontent.1: Going to the moon with the trending crypto: These cryptos have had the most talkability within the last 24 hours, perhaps even with the potential to continue the trend for bigger rise in the near future. Be the one to monitor the prices, charts and data so that you can capture the positive momentum with these popular cryptos today.
Price.Trending.content.2.1: Gate.io cryptocurrency prices and charts show the real-time market of %s+ cryptocurrencies in the world, with not only accurate real-time price trends, but also professional trend analysis. Gate.io helps you grasp the latest updates of the cryptocurrency market instantly.
Price.Trending.content.2.2: Gate.io updates the prices of trending cryptocurrencies in real time, and shows the price changes in the past 1 hour, 24 hours and 7 days, as well as the trading volume in the past 24 hours and the current market value of cryptocurrencies. It also has a clear and concise price trend chart in the past 7 days, which can help you better see the volatilities in the cryptocurrency market.
Price.Trending.title.3: How Do We Calculate the Price of Trending Cryptocurrency?
Price.Trending.content.3.1: The price is calculated using the global trading volume and average price formula, which is based on the pairing available on different exchanges of specific cryptocurrencies.
Price.Trending.content.3.2: The cryptocurrency prices presented by each cryptocurrency exchange are different, but the difference is not significant. The reasons are simply divided into: investment attraction, supply-demand relationship, mining difficulty or hash rate, changes in regulatory policies and volatilities in trending cryptocurrencies. Moreover, each cryptocurrency is traded and circulated in different exchange markets, which has different economic impact and liquidity, and the calculated price will be different.
Price.Trending.title.4: What Is the Best Cryptocurrency to Invest In?
Price.Trending.content.4: The Gate.io cryptocurrency price and chart pages provide you with %s+ different cryptocurrencies, including Bitcoin, Ethereum and Tether, which are currently trending, as well as other tokens with different market values. You can follow and collect this page so that you can follow the trend of cryptocurrency prices for a long time and make a better investment direction.
Price.Trending.title.5: What Causes Certain Cryptos to Become Trending or Popular?
Price.Trending.content.5.1: For a crypto to be trending or popular, there must be obvious positive interest in the market, leading to higher volume of buy transactions and pushing the prices of these crypto tokens up. One can imagine that crypto enthusiasts are shouting that these tokens are about to go “to the moon” all over social media, further driving market interest in these crypto coins.
Price.Trending.content.5.2: Underneath the noise on social media, there are some commonly seen key driving forces contributing to the positive momentum of the trending cryptos. While certain factors are logical, the market has a tendency to be irrational, causing massive price action and fluctuation. This is why it is important to conduct technical analysis in order to determine if it is still the right and safe timing to enter the market.
Price.Trending.title.6: Should I Invest in Crypto Today?
Price.Trending.content.6: It is important to remember that cryptos are subject to extreme market conditions, legal policies, project team management and other unpredictable factors. As such, cryptocurrencies fluctuate greatly and it is important to manage your own risk level. Users are advised to do your own research when making investment decisions in the crypto market.
Price.Gainers.content.1: Going to the moon with the top crypto gainers: These cryptos have had the strongest upward momentum within the last 24 hours, perhaps even with the potential to continue the trend for bigger rise in the near future. Be the one to monitor and capture the positive momentum with these top crypto gainers today.
Price.Gainers.title.2: What Are the Metrics Involved in Determining Top Gainers for the Last 24 Hours?
Price.Gainers.Losers.content.2: The movement of crypto assets based on the real time price action of the past 24 hours.
Price.Gainers.title.3: What Causes Certain Cryptos to Rise as Top Gainers?
Price.Gainers.content.3.1: For a crypto to become a top gainer of the last 24 hours, there must be obvious positive interest in the market, leading to higher volume of buy transactions and pushing the prices of the top gainers up. One can imagine that crypto enthusiasts are shouting that these tokens are about to go “to the moon” all over social media, further driving market interest in the top crypto gainers of the day.
Price.Gainers.content.3.2: Underneath the noise on social media, there are some commonly seen key driving forces contributing to the positive momentum of the top crypto gainers. While certain factors are logical, the market has a tendency to be irrational, causing massive price action and fluctuation. This is why it is important to conduct technical analysis in order to determine if it is still the right and safe timing to enter the market.
Price.Gainers.title.4: Why Do Some Cryptos Become Top Gainers Today Despite being a Small Cap Coin?
Price.Gainers.content.4.1: Small cap coins are usually newer coins in the market, and as such they tend to be less liquid by nature. In positive scenarios, these small caps have experienced teams with strong technical abilities, farsighted project roadmaps and whitepapers as well as excellent track records, just to name some of the factors to be taken into account as fundamental analysis is being carried out. All of these will create interest of genuine early stage investors and can easily drive small caps to become top gainers of the day.
Price.Gainers.content.4.2: However, there are times where small caps become the target of market making by whales and/or malicious market controlling as these cryptos can easily be cornered. That being said, there is a real probability that such crypto gainers could turn out to be pump-and-dump schemes, and investors are advised to tread carefully when dealing with assets of such nature.
Price.Gainers.title.5: Should I Invest in the Top Crypto Gainers Today?
Price.Gainers.content.5: It is possible that the top crypto gainers today may continue to trend. However, it is important to remember that cryptos are subject to extreme market conditions, legal policies, project team management and other unpredictable factors. As such, cryptocurrencies fluctuate greatly and it is important to manage your own risk level. Users are advised to do your own research when making investment decisions in the crypto market.
Price.Losers.content.1: Incoming FUD with the top crypto losers: These cryptos have had the strongest downward momentum within the last 24 hours, perhaps an opportunity for a big rebound in the near future. Be the one to monitor and capture the next opportunity with these top crypto losers today.
Price.Losers.title.2: What Are the Metrics Involved in Determining Top Losers for the Last 24 Hours?
Price.Losers.title.3: What Causes Certain Cryptos to Drop as Top Losers?
Price.Losers.content.3.1: For a crypto to become a top loser of the last 24 hours, there must be significant negative talks spreading in the market, leading to higher volume of buy transactions and pushing the prices of the top losers down. One can imagine that crypto enthusiasts are shouting that these tokens are experiencing FUD all over social media, further driving sell momentum in the top crypto losers of the day.
Price.Losers.content.3.2: Underneath the noise on social media, there are some commonly seen key driving forces contributing to the negative momentum of the top crypto losers. While certain factors are logical, the market has a tendency to be irrational, causing massive price action and fluctuation. This is why it is important to conduct technical analysis in order to determine if it is still the right and safe timing to enter the market.
Price.Losers.title.4: Why Do Some Cryptos Become Top Losers Today Despite being a Big Cap Coin?
Price.Losers.content.4.1: Big cap coins are usually more established coins in the market, and as such they tend to be highly liquid by nature. Generally, these big caps have experienced teams with strong technical abilities, farsighted project roadmaps and whitepapers as well as excellent track records, just to name some of the factors to be taken into account as fundamental analysis is being carried out. All of these will create continued interest of genuine investors and can bring about a rebound, even though the big cap may have been the top loser of the day.
Price.Losers.content.4.2: However, there is always a real probability that such big caps could turn out to be pump-and-dump schemes, and investors are advised to tread carefully when dealing with assets of such nature.
Price.Losers.title.5: Should I Invest in the Top Crypto Losers Today?
Price.Losers.content.5: It is possible that the top crypto losers today may rebound in the future. However, it is important to remember that cryptos are subject to extreme market conditions, legal policies, project team management and other unpredictable factors. As such, cryptocurrencies fluctuate greatly and it is important to manage your own risk level. Users are advised to do your own research when making investment decisions in the crypto market.

Futures Voucher Usage Scenario: Can be used as margin to open positions or pay trading fees in Futures Voucher Mode
Futures Voucher Rules:
1. After receiving the Futures Voucher, you need to manually click on "Deposit Now" to deposit it to your account.

2. You need to switch to the Futures Voucher Mode before using the Futures Voucher.

3. Futures Voucher can be used as margin to offset realized losses when you are trading futures.

4. Futures Voucher Mode is separate from Futures Account, so their positions won't hedge against each other.

5. Assets cannot be transferred in/out in Futures Voucher Mode.

6. You are not responsible for any loss incurred from trading in Futures Voucher Mode; earnings from it will be credited to your Futures Account.

7. Validity period of the Futures Voucher is from its successful deposit till its expiry. Upon expiry, the Futures Voucher will become invalid and the open positions will be closed at market price.

8. Only one Futures Voucher can be used at a time.

9. If you want to use other Futures Voucher, you can manually close the position and destroy the Futures Voucher currently in use.

10. For markets currently support Futures Voucher, please refer to the trading list.

Gate Technology Ltd is a company incorporated in Malta with registration number C89337 and trading under the name‘Gate.MT’.
Gate Technology Ltd is licensed by the Malta Financial Services Authority as a Class 4 Virtual Financial Assets (“VFA”) Services Provider and authorised to provide the following VFA Services to non-experienced investors: (i) the operation of a VFA exchange; and (ii) Custodian or Nominee Services.
Please note that the availability of the products and services on the websites operated by Gate.MT including www.gatemt.com, any associated mobile applications and APIs, any related software, forums, blogs, social media pages and other relevant platforms operated or maintained by Gate.MT (collectively the "Sites") is subject to jurisdictional limitations. Gate.MT may not offer certain products, features and/or services on the Sites in certain jurisdictions due to potential or actual regulatory restrictions, or if it is in Gate.MT’s opinion (in its sole and absolute discretion) that it is not commercial or feasible to provide such products or services in certain jurisdictions.
Other products or services except spot trading, custodian or nominee services offered on the Sites are provided by other group companies and do not fall within the scope of Gate.MT’s regulated services under the VFA licence stipulated above.
Gate Technology Ltd is an independent entity and operates separately from Gate.io. Each legal entity maintains distinct clientele, operations and management.
For the avoidance of doubt, neither Gate.MT nor Gate Technology Ltd are registered nor maintain any address in the Cayman Islands.

ZONE_MEME_DESC: Meme coins are digital assets inspired by humor, pop culture, or internet memes like DOGE and SHIB. They're built on blockchain and used for buying, trading, or storing value. Their worth fluctuates a lot due to social media and pop culture influence, so investing in them requires caution. On social platforms, they're often joked about and get a lot of attention.
ZONE_DEPIN_DESC: DePIN supports the DePIN ecosystem, pays transaction fees, participates in governance decisions, earns ecosystem rewards, and is built on a specific blockchain.
ZONE_AI_DESC: AI tokens are digital assets for AI projects and services. They're used in AI markets, trading algorithms, and decentralized organizations, playing key roles in exchanges and governance.
ZONE_SOLANA_DESC: Solana ecosystem tokens, like SOL and others, are built on the Solana blockchain. They're used for transaction fees, DeFi participation, governance, and rewards. Leveraging Solana's speed and low costs, they offer fast, secure, and affordable transactions.
ZONE_ZKSYNC_DESC: ZkSync ecosystem tokens are built on the ZkSync Layer 2 scaling solution and used for paying transaction fees, participating in DeFi, governance, and rewards. These tokens include ETH (Ethereum's native token) as well as others built on ZkSync.
ZONE_BASE_DESC: Base is an Ethereum Layer 2 scaling solution built on Optimism's OP Stack technology, offering security, low costs, and developer-friendly features.
ZONE_BLAST_DESC: Blast is an Ethereum Layer 2 network created by the Blur team, introducing a ecosystem network featuring passive income, gas fees, and airdrops as its three distinctive functionalities.
ZONE_LAYER2_DESC: Layer 2 tokens are digital assets built on Layer 2 scaling solutions, typically used for paying transaction fees, participating in DeFi, governance, and rewards. They are based on Layer 2 technology, offering fast, inexpensive transactions, and settling on blockchain.
ZONE_ETH_2_STAKING_DESC: ETH liquidity staking is a cryptocurrency staking method where users can stake tokens and earn rewards. Through liquidity staking protocols, users represent ownership and earnings in the staking pool, gaining access to liquidity staking derivatives.
ZONE_METAVERSE_DESC: Metaverse is a virtual digital world that combines virtual reality, augmented reality, and blockchain technology, allowing users to create, interact with, and trade digitized three-dimensional spaces and assets.
ZONE_NFT_DESC: NFTs, or Non-Fungible Tokens, are unique, non-replaceable digital assets based on blockchain technology that prove ownership and support the trading and collecting of digital assets. They foster innovative applications in art, gaming, virtual assets, and beyond.
ZONE_STORAGE_DESC: Storage-type tokens are characterized by their support for storage space transactions, usage in storing and retrieving data, rewarding storage providers, ensuring data security and privacy, and applicability in decentralized applications.
ZONE_POLKA_DESC: Polkadot tokens are the native tokens of the Polkadot ecosystem, used for paying fees, governance, staking, and rewards. The ecosystem boasts cross-chain interoperability, scalability, governance, self-upgradability, and diverse DApps.
ZONE_DEFI_DESC: DeFi tokens are blockchain-based digital assets used to support the decentralized finance (DeFi) ecosystem, including paying fees, participating in governance, and receiving rewards.
ZONE_BRC20_DESC: BRC-20 is a standard for homogeneous tokens based on the Bitcoin network, created through the Ordinal protocol, enabling users to deploy token contracts, issue, and transfer homogeneous tokens on the Bitcoin network.
ZONE_RUNES_DESC: Runes is a new protocol introduced on the Bitcoin network, allowing users to locally create and transfer interchangeable tokens on Bitcoin.
ZONE_NEWLISTED_DESC: Tokens traded within 30 days of listing.
ZONE_ETF_DESC: Trading products with inherent leverage and automatic rebalancing mechanisms.
ZONE_5ETF_DESC: Trading products with leverage attributes and automatic rebalancing mechanisms, typically exhibiting price fluctuations approximately five times that of the underlying asset market.
ZONE_EXCHANGE_DESC: A class of tokens issued by digital currency trading platforms and used within the platform to help achieve platform functionalities.

Futures Voucher Rules New:
1. After receiving the Futures Voucher, you need to manually click on "Activate" to activate it.

2. You need to switch to the Futures Voucher Mode before using the Futures Voucher.

3. Futures Voucher can be used as margin to offset realized losses when you are trading futures.

4. Futures Voucher Mode is separate from Futures Account, so their positions won’t hedge against each other.

5. Assets cannot be transferred in/out in Futures Voucher Mode.

6. You are not responsible for any loss incurred from trading in Futures Voucher Mode; earnings from it will be credited to your Futures Account.

7. Validity period of the Futures Voucher is from its successful activation till its expiry. Upon expiry, the Futures Voucher will become invalid and the open positions will be closed at market price.

8. Only one Futures Voucher can be used at a time.

9. If you want to use other Futures Voucher, you can manually close the position and destroy the Futures Voucher currently in use.

10. For markets currently support Futures Voucher, please refer to the trading list.

Commission.Rebate.Rule:
1. Spot and futures trades during the effective period of the Trading Fee Rebate Voucher can enjoy the trading fee rebate.

2. The trading fee rebate will be credited to the spot account on the day following the trades before 23:59:59 (UTC+0).

3. Rebate Amount = Net Trading Fee Paid Daily * Rebate Percentage. Net Trading Fee refers to the actual paid trading fee after deducting the VIP discounts, Payment in Points, Referral and other commissions.

4. Futures trading fee rebate only supports USDT-M Perpetual Futures. Delivery Futures, Bots, Copy and trades using Futures Bonus or Futures Voucher cannot enjoy rebates.

5. The daily trading fee rebate will only be credited when the amount is greater than 0.0000000001 USDT.

6. During the effective period of the Trading Fee Rebate Voucher, trades generated in the applicable markets will enjoy rebates in chronological order.

7. Trading Fee Rebate Voucher should be manually activated to take effect and only one voucher can be activated at a time. The voucher becomes invalid upon expiry, and the balance of the voucher can no longer be used for rebates.

8. The maximum rebate amount each time equals the balance of the Rebate Voucher.

9. The trading markets must be consistent with the applicable markets of the Rebate Voucher.

10. When the currency of the trade is inconsistent with the currency of the Rebate Voucher, the trading fee will be calculated based on the real-time fee rate, converted to USDT, and then credited to the user's spot account.

11. Rebate Voucher is non-transferable and non-withdrawable.

ETH2_FAQ_MAIN:
### What is ETH staking?
As a proof-of-stake network, Ethereum allows its holders to stake their ETH to secure the network and earn rewards. However, staking directly through the Ethereum network requires at least32 ETH.
Gate.io streamlines ETH onchain staking by running node on behalf of users and allowing a minimum of 0.000001 ETH staking threshold. After staking ETH at Gate.io, you will get ETH2 as the tokenized representation of your staked ETH and rewards.
### What is ETH2 and what can I do with it?
ETH2 is a reward-generating liquid staking token and the representation of your staked ETH at a 1:1 ratio.
ETH2 provides you with higher liquidity and more return opportunities besides earning rewards, including:
·  ETH2/ETH & ETH2/USDT spot trading
· Use ETH2 as your loan collateral
### ETH Staking 
If you start staking during 00:00~23:59 (UTC), you will be able to check your rewards in the form of ETH2 in your spot account from the next day.
MIN Staking Amount 0.000001 ETH
Daily Max Staking Amount per Person 0.000001 ETH
Conversion Rate 1ETH=1ETH2
Term Flexible
### ETH Redeeming
As a ETH2 holder you can redeem your ETH2 back to EHT at a 1:1 ratio. Your staking amount will be returned to your account immediately after submitting a redemption request.
The count of staking and redemption is limited to max 20 times per day.
### How will my rewards be calculated?
After staking ETH, rewards will be released in the form of ETH2 based on the amount of staked ETH.
Est. APR is calculated based on the total amount of ETH2 rewards earned by Gate.io validators on the Ethereum blockchain and is subject to daily market fluctuations.
ETH2 rewards = ETH2 holding * daily APR/365
### When will the max staking amount be reset?
The daily max stake and redeem limit resets every 24 hours, starting from the time of your first stake or redeem operation.
ETH2_FAQ_COMMON:
### Advantages of Gate.io ETH2.0
Gate.io provides a flexible ETH2.0 staking solution to users based on its securely running Ethereum infrastructure and mature asset management solution. The advantages are as follows: 
 
 Great Capital Efficiency
 
Users can buy or sell ETH2 in USDT and ETH markets freely.
 
ETH2 token is also a certificate for participating in ETH2.0 Staking. By holding ETH2, you are participating in ETH2.0 Staking.
 
Participating in Gate.io ETH2.0 Staking will not affect your VIP tier, and you can still enjoy all privileges of your VIP tier.
 
Gate.io is committed to maintaining users' VIP privileges while they are participating in ETH2.0 Staking for a more comprehensive and seamless trading experience.
 
Steady Return
 
Gate.io will distribute the net income from ETH2.0 Staking to EHT2 holders.
 
The staking reward is distributed in the form of ETH2 based on users' average ETH2 holdings over a period of 14 days.
 
The APR of ETH2.0 Staking is related to the amount of ETH being staked. The yield tends to be higher at an early stage as less ETH is being staked. In the long term, the yield is expected to be stable around 3%-10%.
 
Low Entry Barrier
 
ETH2.0 Staking has a relatively high entry barrier for ordinary users as participants need to hold at least 32 ETH.
 
However, in Gate.io, you can participate in ETH2.0 Staking by simply buying or converting to ETH2 tokens and earn on-chain rewards.
### Gate.io ETH2.0 solution
Improve Scalability
 
ETH1.0 only supports about 15 transactions per second. After the ETH2.0 upgrade, it will eventually be divided into 64 (maybe more in the future) shards, which theoretically enables the network to complete thousands or even tens of thousands of transactions per second. ETH2.0 solves the problem that the computing power of the main network is too concentrated, and further improves the scalability.
 
Environmental Sustainability
 
Currently, Ethereum is using the PoW mechanism to operate and safeguard the network security. Despite PoW's advantages of ensuring security and decentralization, it is expensive for nodes to safeguard the security of the network. In the end, only one node can find the correct hash value and get the block reward. But all the global participating nodes have paid enormous computing power and electricity, which is not only inefficient but also a waste of environmental resources. While upgrading to the PoS consensus mechanism, ETH will no longer rely on tremendous computing power and electricity to maintain and operate the network but rely on token-staking equity verification to create blocks and trade on the chain.
### Roadmap of ETH 2.0 development
Like ETH 1.0, ETH 2.0 is also divided into several phases. And the most important of these are Phase 0, Phase 1 and Phase 2.
 
Phase 0: Beacon Chain
 
This is the very first phase of ETH2 which will implement the beacon chain. As a new chain, beacon chain is responsible for validators' participation of stakings, so as to maintain the network. It is also the order and control center of the ETH 2.0 eco. ETH 2.0 network in phase 0 does not support functions such as smart contracts, asset transfers and so on. The only available program is verification. Users can not transfer their assets to an exchange in this phase.
 
Phase 1: Sharding
 
The goal of phase 1 mainly is to integrate ETH 1.0 with ETH 2.0. A shard chain essentially is an expansion mechanism of the ETH network, which splits the ETH blockchain into 64 different chains and distributes the data processing tasks to many nodes, allowing them to process these data in parallel. Each shade chain acts as a diversion lane of the congested ETH networks, so as to dramatically improve the processing capacity of the network and produce a higher throughput.
 
[Click to get the sharding roadmap](https://ethereum.org)
 
Phase 2: Execution
 
The current definitions and functions of phase 2 are still under exploration. Phase 2 will comprehensively improve the sharding functions.Each shard will govern EVM based on eWASM and be compatible with smart contracts and, at the same time, can transfer, withdraw and cross-shard transfer. This phase will finish the integration of ETH 1.0 and ETH 2.0. and put an end to the PoW consensus mechanism.
### How to become a validator of ETH 2.0?
 
At first, users need to stake 32 ether to the deposit contract: `https://etherscan.io/address/0x00000000219ab540356cBB839Cbe05303d7705Fa#tokentxns` Then they should run both ETH 1.0 and ETH 2.0 terminals at the same time to become a validator. As a validator, the node must keep online for a long time. Validators will get a reward from ETH when they successfully verified one block, with an APR of staking interest of about 5-10%. However, if the validator missed the task of verification of the ETH network allocated by the beacon chain due being offline, he would be fined. Malicious and wrong verification will lead to confiscating the staked 32 Ether.
 
The ETH staked to the deposit contract is an irreversible transaction. Validators will have a possibility to transfer their funds until ETH 2.0 reaches phase 1. Consequently, it still needs two or three years for ETH 2.0 to completely have access to sharding and smart contracts, which means that validators will face the risk of being incapable of withdrawing ETH for at least 2 years. In addition, once mortgaged to the beacon chain, ETH will generate BETH and can not return to the ETH 1.0 mainchain. If ETH 2.0 fails to upgrade, losses may occur to users. As a result, it is not recommended that ordinary users become validators.
### ETH2.0 Staking enabled on Gate.io
 
Following the ETH2.0 Phase 0 launch, ETH holders will be able to participate in PoS staking by depositing their ETH on ETH2.0 to earn rewards.
 
Taking part in ETH2.0 staking is not easy. It demands a general higher technical expertise, and requires a long staking time. Moreover, you must run a validator on both the ETH1.0 chain and the ETH2.0 Beacon Chain at the same time and maintain a stable staking status while doing so. Otherwise, your funds in staking may be charged penalties.
### ETH2 token transaction
 
Due to the high barriers of entry, ETH2.0 Staking is not suitable for every user. To give all users a chance to participate in ETH2.0 Staking, Gate.io will provide a flexible ETH2.0 Staking solution to users, based on our stably running Ethereum infrastructure and mature asset management solution. With this solution, users can earn a staking reward while not needing to lock their ETH in ETH2.0 for a long time or worry about ETH2.0 penalties. Below you can find more details about our ETH2.0 Staking solution.
1. Gate.io will list ETH2 tokens, which will be the certificate for users to participate in ETH2 staking. 1 ETH2 represents 1 ETH locked in ETH2 staking. Holding ETH2 is equal to participating in ETH2 staking.
2. Users will be able to buy or sell ETH2 on USDT and ETH markets freely.
3. Gate.io will distribute the net income (staking reward minus cost) from ETH2.0 staking to ETH2 holders as ETH2.0 staking starts.
4. The staking reward will be in the form of ETH2, distributed based on users' average ETH2 holdings over a period of 14 days.
5. Currently, validators are waiting in line for the chance of staking on ETH2.0. It may take a few days to start staking after ETH2 launches (the delay may vary, depending on the length of the waiting list).
6. The APR of ETH2.0 staking is related to the amount of ETH being staked. The yield tends to be higher at an early stage as less ETH is being staked. In the long term, the yield is expected to be stable, around 5%-10%.

COIN_STAKING_MAIN:
### 1. What is GT Staking?
  GT Staking is the process of participating in the Gate.io Proof of Stake (PoS) consensus mechanism, during which GT holders stake their GTs to protect the network and earn rewards.
Gate.io streamlines GT on-chain staking by running node on behalf of users and providing a minimum of 1 GT staking threshold. After staking GT at Gate.io, you will get GT2 as the tokenized representation of your staked GT and rewards.。
### 2. GT Staking Rules
  If you stake GT on a given calendar day (00:00 - 23:59 UTC), staking reward will be released in the form of GT2 the next day.
  The minimum staking amount is 1 GT.
### 3. GT Redemption Rules
  As a GT2 holder, you can redeem your GT2 back to GT at a 1:1 ratio. Your principal and return will be credited to your account immediately after submitting a redemption request.
Redemption is limited to a maximum of 1,000,000 GT within 24 hours.
COIN_STAKING_COMMON:
### 1. Why is the Est. APR changing and how is it calculated?
  The Est. APR is dynamically changing on a daily basis along with on-chain staked principal and returns. In order to ensure the sustainability of the product, 5% of the staking rewards will be charged as a staking fee. Staking reward will be released the next day after staking.
### 2. How is my return calculated?
  After staking GT, rewards will be released in the form of GT2 based on the amount of staked GT.
  Est. APR is calculated based on the total amount of GT2 reward earned by Gate.io validators on the Gate.io blockchain and is subject to daily market fluctuations.
  GT2 return = GT2 holding amount × daily APR / 365 × (1 - staking fee)
### 3. How long does it take to receive rewards after staking?
  If you stake on day D, interest will be distributed on D+1.
### 4. Can I redeem my GT2 return at any time?
  GT2 returns can be redeemed at any time and will be credited to your account immediately after submitting the redemption request.
### 5. Is GT2 safe?
  GT2 is safe and secure and can be redeemed for GT at any time on the GT Staking page.
### 6. Does GT Staking require identity verification?
  Yes. Participation in GT Staking requires completing the identity verification first.
### 7. Can I use sub-accounts to participate in GT Staking?
   Yes. Sub-accounts are supported for GT Staking.
### 8. Can I cancel a staking or redemption order after submission?
   No. The order cannot be canceled. But you can stake or redeem your GT again through GT Staking at any time.

SOL_COIN_STAKING_MAIN:
### What is SOL Staking? 
SOL Staking is an on-chain staking product of Gate.io,  which allows users to stake SOL and delegate it to validators on Solana through Gate.io. Users can also easily earn on-chain rewards.
 ### SOL Staking Rules 
If you stake SOL on a given calendar day (00:00 - 23:59 UTC), staking reward will be released in the form of SOL2 the next day.
The minimum staking amount is 0.1 SOL.
 ### SOL Redemption Rules 
As a SOL2 holder, you can redeem your SOL2 back to SOL at a 1:1 ratio. Your principal and return will be credited to your account immediately after submitting a redemption request.
Redemption is limited to a maximum of 43,750 SOL within 24 hours.
SOL_COIN_STAKING_COMMON:
### Why is the Est. APR changing and how is it calculated? 
The Est. APR is dynamically changing on a daily basis along with on-chain staked principal and returns. In order to ensure the sustainability of the product, 5% of the staking rewards will be charged as a staking fee. Staking reward will be released the next day after staking.
 ### How is my return calculated? 
After staking SOL, rewards will be released in the form of SOL2 based on the amount of staked SOL. 
Est. APR is calculated based on the total amount of SOL2 reward earned by Gate.io validators on the Gatechain blockchain and is subject to daily market fluctuations. 
SOL2 return = SOL2 holding amount × daily APR / 365 × (1 - staking fee)
 ### How long does it take to receive rewards after staking? 
If you stake on day D, interest will be distributed on D+1.
 ### Can I redeem my SOL2 return at any time? 
SOL2 returns can be redeemed at any time and will be credited to your account immediately after submitting the redemption request.
 ### Is SOL2 safe? 
SOL2 is safe and secure and can be redeemed for SOL at any time on the SOL Staking page.
 ### Does SOL Staking require identity verification? 
Yes. Participation in SOL Staking requires completing the identity verification first.
 ### Can I use sub-accounts to participate in SOL Staking? 
Yes.Sub-accounts are supported for SOL Staking.
 ### Can I cancel a staking or redemption order after submission? 
No. The order cannot be canceled. But you can stake or redeem your SOL again through SOL Staking at any time.
USDE_COIN_STAKING_MAIN:
### What is USDE Staking?
USDE Staking is an on-chain staking product of Gate.io, which allows users to stake USDE and delegate it to validators on Ethena through Gate.io. Users can also easily earn on-chain rewards.
### USDE Staking Rules 
If you stake USDE on a given calendar day (00:00 - 23:59 UTC), staking reward will be released on D+2.
The minimum staking amount is 10 USDE.
### USDE Redemption Rules 
As a USDE holder, you can redeem your USDE at any time. Your principal and return will be credited to your account on D+7 after submitting the redemption request. 
Redemption is limited to a maximum of 1,000,000 USDE within 24 hours.
USDE_COIN_STAKING_COMMON:
### Why is the Est. APR changing and how is it calculated?
The Est. APR of USDE Staking is dynamically changing on a daily basis along with on-chain staked principal and returns.
 ### How is my return calculated? 
After staking USDE,  rewards will be released in the form of USDE based on the amount of staked USDE.
The Est. daily APR is calculated based on the total amount of USDE rewards earned by all Gate.io validators on Ethena and is subject to daily market fluctuations
USDE return = USDE staking amount * daily APR / 365 
 ### How long does it take to receive rewards after staking?
If you stake on day D, interest starts to accrue on D+1 and is paid on D+2.
 ### Can I redeem my USDE return at any time? 
 USDE returns can be redeemed at any time and will be credited to your account in the form of USDE on D+7 after submitting the redemption request.
 ### Is USDE safe? 
USDE is safe and secure and can be redeemed to USDE at any time on the USDE Staking page.
 ### Does USDE Staking require identity verification? 
Yes. Participation in USDE Staking requires completing the identity verification first.
 ### Can I use sub-accounts to participate in USDE Staking?
Yes. Sub-accounts are supported for USDE Staking.
 ### Can I cancel a staking or redemption order after submission?
No. The order cannot be canceled. But you can stake or redeem your USDE again through USDE Staking at any time.
